# =============================================================================
# Vayumi browser client — configuration reference
# =============================================================================
# This folder is static HTML/JS. Browsers do not read .env files automatically.
# Use this file as documentation for what endpoints the client should use.
#
# Practical options:
#   • Hardcode or edit the base URL / WebSocket URL in app.js where requests
#     are made (typical for Phase 1).
#   • Or add a gitignored config.local.js that sets window.__VAYUMI_CONFIG__
#     and read it from app.js.
#   • If you later add Vite/Webpack, rename to .env and use VITE_* prefixes.
# =============================================================================

# REST API (same host:port as FastAPI)
# VAYUMI_API_BASE=http://localhost:8000

# WebSocket realtime endpoint
# VAYUMI_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8000/ws/vayumi
